plan.adaptiveSpec:
ADAPTIVE PLACEMENT TEST — buildable Dart spec (replaces the 3-item fixed quiz in onboarding_flow.dart)

=== θ LADDER (the "calibrated bank", 7 rungs idx 0..6) ===
0=5級(A1−), 1=4級(A1−), 2=3級(A1), 3=準2級(A2), 4=準2級プラス(A2+), 5=2級(B1), 6=準1級(B2). Cap at 6 (1級/C1 out of child scope). Each item is tagged with grade(rung) + skill(vocab|grammar|readingGist) + correctIndex + 4 SAME-TYPE choices.

=== 1. START POINT (age prior — biggest item-saver) ===
Seed θ̂ (double) from OnboardingResult.ageYears, NOT from zero:
  age<=6 → 0(5級) ; 7-9 → 1(4級) ; 10-12 → 2(3級) ; 13-15 → 3(準2級) ; 16+ → 4(準2級プラス).
Optional one-tap self-report ("英語を習ったことは？" ない/少し/得意) shifts seed by -1/0/+1, clamped [0,6]. This is the informative prior; a 13-yo never starts at "Dog=いぬ".

=== 2. ITEM SELECTION (max-information ≈ target current estimate) ===
Each step: pick an UNUSED item whose grade == round(θ̂). Discrete analogue of "select max Fisher information at θ̂" (info maximized when P(correct)≈0.5, i.e. an item AT the estimate). Track asked item ids to avoid repeats within and across sessions.

=== 3. SCORING / ABILITY UPDATE (damped EWMA ascent, child-robust) ===
After each answer:
  step = max(0.5, 1.5 - 0.25*n)   // big early jumps to find region, fine settle later; n = items answered so far
  correct → θ̂ += step ; wrong → θ̂ -= step ; clamp θ̂ to [0.0,6.0]
NON-DISCOURAGE GUARD (mandatory for under-16s): after a WRONG answer, the next item's grade = floor(θ̂) (a slightly easier, winnable item) — never present two consecutive items a child just failed; the test must never spiral into a failure streak.

=== 4. STOPPING RULE (few items: 4-8) ===
Stop when EITHER:
  • SETTLED (ceiling found): last 3 items at the same rung r AND pattern is "passes r, fails r+1" → place at r. Typically 4-6 items.
  • MAX LENGTH: hard cap of 8 items (attention budget for 6-10 yo).
  • MIN LENGTH: never stop before 3 items (no single lucky/unlucky tap decides).

=== 5. FINAL PLACEMENT ===
placementGrade = highest rung r where child answered >=2/3 of presented r-items correctly AND did NOT clear r+1.
RETENTION RULE: if child only BARELY cleared the ceiling (e.g. 2/3, volatile), start the adventure ONE rung BELOW the ceiling — kinder, builds momentum.
Return PlacementOutcome{ grade:0..6, eikenLevel:'5'|'4'|'3'|'pre2'|'pre2plus'|'2'|'pre1', cefr, confidence:high|medium|low }. confidence=low (hit max length, still volatile) → start at the conservative (lower) rung; persist final θ̂ so in-game performance / a re-test can nudge placement later (ties into T12 adaptive difficulty).

=== DART SKETCH (the controller) ===
class PlacementItem { final int grade; final String skill; final String stemEn; final String? stemJa; final List<String> choices; final int correctIndex; }

class PlacementEngine {
  double theta;
  final List<int> askedGrades = [];
  final Set<int> usedItemIds = {};
  final List<bool> answers = [];
  int get n => answers.length;
  PlacementEngine.fromAge(int age, {int selfReportShift = 0})
      : theta = (_seed(age) + selfReportShift).clamp(0.0, 6.0);
  static double _seed(int a) => a<=6?0 : a<=9?1 : a<=12?2 : a<=15?3 : 4;
  int nextGrade() {                                   // §2 + §3 guard
    if (answers.isNotEmpty && !answers.last) return theta.floor().clamp(0,6);
    return theta.round().clamp(0,6);
  }
  void record(bool ok) {                              // §3
    final step = math.max(0.5, 1.5 - 0.25*n);
    theta = (theta + (ok ? step : -step)).clamp(0.0, 6.0);
    answers.add(ok);
  }
  bool get done {                                     // §4
    if (n < 3) return false;
    if (n >= 8) return true;
    return _ceilingStable();                          // last 3 same rung, passed r / failed r+1
  }
  PlacementOutcome result() { /* §5 highest rung >=2/3 correct & next failed; barely-cleared → -1; volatile → low conf */ }
}

Controller drives the loop: build PlacementEngine.fromAge(result.ageYears), then while(!done){ g=nextGrade(); item=bank.unusedItemForGrade(g); show; record(tapped==item.correctIndex); }. On done → PlacementOutcome → map grade→eikenLevel string → start quest (see wiring below).
